explanation: The solution uses a simple while loop to iteratively apply the given operations until n becomes 1. It takes advantage of the properties of even and odd numbers to minimize the number of operations. When n is even, it simply divides by 2. When n is odd, it checks whether n is of the form 4k+1 or n=3 (in which case subtracting 1 results in a number divisible by 4, leading to more efficient reduction) or 4k+3 (in which case adding 1 is more efficient). This greedy approach ensures the minimum number of operations.

